   <dc:title>Handwritten letter from Schenker to Evelina Pairamall, dated November 12,
    1913</dc:title>

   <dcterms:created>1913-11-12T12:00:00Z</dcterms:created>
   <dcterms:dateSubmitted>2022-03-18</dcterms:dateSubmitted>
   <dc:description>Schenker thanks Evelina Pairamall warmly for sending him an article by
    Saint-Saens on manuscripts in Berlin, which covers an autograph manuscript of Beethoven's Ninth
    Symphony, and reports to her his own work on another autograph of that work. -- He asks if she
    is returning to Vienna soon, and promises to show her his discoveries, concluding with a joke
    employing musical technical terms.</dc:description>
   <dc:subject/>


   <marcrel:correspondent key="entity-000632">HSchenker</marcrel:correspondent>
